{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"alias":"holy-heartfelt-pheasant","description":"# S1 ‚Äî Optional Streamable-HTTP transport for rebar-mcp + transport hardening\n\n## Why\nAuthentication in MCP is an HTTP-transport concern; the spec says stdio servers must not\nauthenticate. rebar-mcp is stdio-only today (`src/rebar/mcp_server.py`, `build_server().run()`\nwith no transport arg). Before any verifier can exist there must be an HTTP transport to\nauthenticate against. This story adds that transport and its network hardening ‚Äî the foundation\nevery auth story builds on ‚Äî with stdio unchanged as the default.\n\n## What\nAdd an **optional Streamable-HTTP transport** to rebar-mcp, selected by config, and its\ntransport-security hardening, using the official `mcp` SDK's native support:\n- Extend `McpConfig` (`src/rebar/_config_schema.py`) with `transport` (`stdio` default | `http`),\n  `http_host` (default `127.0.0.1`), `http_port` (default `8000`), `http_path` (default `/mcp`),\n  `http_allowed_hosts`, `http_allowed_origins` ‚Äî auto-deriving `REBAR_MCP_*` env vars via the\n  existing coercer pattern; register them in `MCP_ENV_VARS` and `server.json` (the CI drift gate\n  `scripts/check_server_manifest.py` must pass).\n- In `build_server`/`main`, when `transport=http` construct `FastMCP(\"rebar\", host=‚Ä¶, port=‚Ä¶,\n  transport_security=TransportSecuritySettings(enable_dns_rebinding_protection=True,\n  allowed_hosts=‚Ä¶, allowed_origins=‚Ä¶))` and run via `run(transport=\"streamable-http\")`; stdio\n  path unchanged.\n- Secure defaults: DNS-rebinding/Origin protection **on**; loopback bind default; a non-loopback\n  `http_host` requires a non-empty `http_allowed_hosts`/`http_allowed_origins` or the server\n  refuses to start (fail-closed ‚Äî avoids the SDK's historical default-off DNS-rebinding class,\n  GHSA-9h52-p55h-vw2f, and the \"421\" late-host footgun).\n- **Unauthenticated-HTTP guard:** starting `transport=http` with no auth configured refuses to\n  start unless `REBAR_MCP_ALLOW_UNAUTHENTICATED_HTTP` is truthy (auth config itself lands in S2;\n  this story reads a not-yet-populated \"auth enabled\" as false, so HTTP requires the explicit ack\n  until S2 ‚Äî an intentional safe default).\n\n## Approach & rationale\nUse the SDK's built-in Streamable-HTTP transport and `TransportSecuritySettings` rather than\nhand-rolling an ASGI server ‚Äî the SDK already provides both, keeping this a thin wiring change\non a blessed seam and consistent with how peer servers (GitHub/Grafana/Neon) expose HTTP. Set\n`host`/`port`/`transport_security` at `FastMCP(...)` construction (not via late attribute\nassignment, which the SDK does not re-derive ‚Äî the documented \"421\" bug).\n\n## Scope\nThis story: the transport + transport-security + the unauthenticated-HTTP refusal only. It ships\n**no** token verifiers and does **not** validate any token (that is S2+). A subset of the epic.\n\n## Security\nCrosses a trust boundary (opens a network listener). Mitigated here by: DNS-rebinding/Origin\nallowlisting on by default, loopback-only bind by default, mandatory allowlist for non-loopback,\nand the fail-closed unauthenticated-HTTP refusal. TLS is assumed terminated at an edge proxy\n(documented in S7); rebar binds HTTP behind it.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `McpConfig` exposes `transport`/`http_host`/`http_port`/`http_path`/`http_allowed_hosts`/\n      `http_allowed_origins`; unset ‚Üí stdio, byte-identical to today (observable: existing\n      `tests/interfaces/facades/test_mcp.py` stdio suite still passes).\n- [ ] Integration test (tier: integration ‚Äî httpx `ASGITransport` against\n      `mcp.streamable_http_app()` under `mcp.session_manager.run()`; a unit test cannot cross the\n      Starlette transport/middleware seam) boots the server with `transport=http` and asserts a\n      baseline MCP request succeeds over HTTP (observable oracle: HTTP 200 + a valid\n      `initialize` response).\n- [ ] Integration test asserts a request with a disallowed `Host`/`Origin` is rejected\n      (observable oracle: HTTP 421 for bad Host / 403 for bad Origin) while an allowed one passes\n      ‚Äî with a negative-control allowed request in the same test.\n- [ ] Unit/integration test asserts `transport=http` with a non-loopback `http_host` and empty\n      allowlists refuses to start (observable oracle: process exits non-zero / raises with a clear\n      message), and passes when the allowlist is supplied.\n- [ ] Unit/integration test asserts `transport=http` with no auth and no\n      `REBAR_MCP_ALLOW_UNAUTHENTICATED_HTTP` refuses to start, and starts when the ack is set.\n- [ ] `MCP_ENV_VARS` + `server.json` include the new keys and `scripts/check_server_manifest.py`\n      passes (observable oracle: the manifest drift test is green).\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` pass.\n\n## Compatibility\nAdditive: stdio remains default; all new keys default to today's behavior when unset. No change\nto the existing 48 tools or the stdio path.","id":"37dc-0a2d-8907-442d","parent_id":"3393-83ca-5501-4e6e","priority":1,"tags":["mcp","auth"],"ticket_type":"story","title":"S1 ‚Äî Optional Streamable-HTTP transport for rebar-mcp + transport hardening"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784060317344278001,"uuid":"c84ac193-ce4f-4976-894a-4f6e76b4a909"}